      "id": "C",
      "text": "8%"
    },
    {
      "id": "D",
      "text": "11%"
    }
  ],
  "correct_option": "C",
  "answer_text": "C",
  "answer_format": "option_letter",
  "solution": "**Step 1: Identify Cash Flows**: Annual NOI = $120,000; Terminal Value = $1,500,000; Discount Rate = 8% (0.08). **Step 2: Calculate PV of NOIs**: PV = $120,000 × [(1 - (1 + 0.08)^-3) / 0.08] + ($1,500,000 / (1 + 0.08)^3). **Step 3: Solve**: PV of NOIs = $120,000 × 2.5771 = $309,253. Terminal PV = $1,500,000 / 1.2597 ≈ $1,189,207. Total NPV = $309,253 + $1,189,207 = $1,498,460, rounding to $1,500,000."
